entry.name: Study 3 - LTQ-OrbitrapO@65
entry.description: TRANCHE KEY: c5V9k5CM71JMvBiMLb/0xG6OUteG9TLrKLR0nLQOJAzeoNRzIns1bFlXGj/sEAHfSGre8ZxmjxUuJSG8Z4UMfbfTYjgAAAAAAAAF0w== The Unbiased Discovery Working Group tested a new version of the SOP for the complex yeast lysate sample introduced in this study. Each instrument was evaluated for SOP v2.0, specifying 184-minute RPLC analyses, in two replicates of NCI-20 followed by yeast lysate. For this study only, an Applied Biosystems QSTAR-Elite accompanied the LTQ and Orbitrap instruments.
